comments:
A detached part of the parish of Axminster was transferred 
    from Devon to Dorset on 20.10.1844; this area became part of the parish of 
    Thorncombe on 25.3.1884, so that thereafter Axminster was 
    entirely in Devon. Abolished 1.4.1915 
    to become the separate parishes of Axminster Town and Axminster Hamlets.

Transferred from Dorset to Devon on 2.7.1896. See also Table 2, 
    note (f).

Transferred from Dorset to Devon on 30.9.1896. See also Table 
    2, note (f).
Abolished 1894 to become the separate parishes of Seaton and Beer.
